metadata.source: Dane Rudhyar - An Astrological Mandala: The Cycle of Transformations and Its 360 Symbolic Phases
metadata.notes: Sabian Symbols revealed by Elsie Wheeler, interpreted by Marc Edmund Jones, expanded by Dane Rudhyar
metadata.usage: Match planet degree (round to nearest integer, 1-30) with sign to find symbol

aries.symbol: A woman just risen from the sea. A seal is embracing her.
aries.keynote: Emergence of new forms and of the potency of the urge toward self-manifestation.

aries.symbol: A comedian reveals human nature.
aries.keynote: The capacity to perceive and show to others the humor inherent in any life situation.

aries.symbol: A cameo profile of a man, in the outline of his country.
aries.keynote: The power of clearly defined ideals and group-goals in enhancing the growth of the individual.

aries.symbol: Two lovers strolling through a secluded walk.
aries.keynote: The blessing bestowed upon personal achievement by the spiritualization of the sex urge.

aries.symbol: A triangle with wings.
aries.keynote: The spiritual blessing which strengthens individuals who, early in life, are able to accept the full responsibility of their destiny.

aries.symbol: A square brightly lighted on one side.
aries.keynote: The revelation, beyond an ego-viewpoint, of the essential nature of any being's well-established structure.

aries.symbol: A man successfully expressing himself in two realms at once.
aries.keynote: The ability to function satisfactorily in strictly human and intellectual situations as well as in inner realms of transcendent realization.

aries.symbol: A large hat with streamers flying, facing east.
aries.keynote: The need to be socially relevant and to 'serve' the needs of the period, whatever one's own desires may be.

aries.symbol: A crystal gazer.
aries.keynote: The development of an inner realization of organic wholeness.

aries.symbol: A teacher gives new symbolic forms to traditional images.
aries.keynote: The need to incorporate a vast array of information within a framework allowing the student to grasp the hidden side of what we accept as empirical data.

aries.symbol: The ruler of a nation.
aries.keynote: The power inherent in the competent and wise guidance of the collective activities of a group of responsible persons.

aries.symbol: A triangularly shaped flight of wild geese.
aries.keynote: Ideals that has a compelling power over the souls of a group who respond in full consciousness to its magnetic appeal.

aries.symbol: An unsuccessful bomb explosion.
aries.keynote: A comforting realization that all things are bound to fail when attempted prematurely.

aries.symbol: A serpent coiling near a man and a woman.
aries.keynote: Deeply rooted in past experiences, the secret longing for forbidden memories.

aries.symbol: An Indian weaving a blanket.
aries.keynote: The wholesome reliance upon one's own individual inner resources, and the serenity born of the sense of communion with the Mother Force.

aries.symbol: Brownies dancing in the setting sun.
aries.keynote: The guidance and help of invisible 'companions' ever ready to provide necessary assistance to the earnest striver.

aries.symbol: Two prim spinsters.
aries.keynote: The immature boldness that a second-hand knowledge of life or a theoretical idealism may produce when confronted with the rich vitality of actual experience.

aries.symbol: An empty hammock.
aries.keynote: The need to balance activity and rest, and to seek contact with deeper levels of being.

aries.symbol: The magic carpet of Oriental imagery.
aries.keynote: The use of creative imagination in dealing with practical problems.

aries.symbol: A young girl feeding birds in winter.
aries.keynote: The kindness and compassionate assistance that is the law of life in all realms of being.

aries.symbol: A pugilist entering the ring.
aries.keynote: The release and glorification of social aggressiveness.

aries.symbol: The gate to the garden of all fulfilled desires.
aries.keynote: The reward for having faithfully and fully devoted one's whole being to a goal that transcends individualistic values.

aries.symbol: A woman in pastel colors carrying a heavy and valuable but veiled load.
aries.keynote: The gift of spiritual power which an individual who has fulfilled his evolutionary task holds in trust for his fellows.

aries.symbol: Blown inward by the wind, the curtains of an open window take the shape of a cornucopia.
aries.keynote: The constant interplay between the individual's need for self-actualization and his environment's response to this need.

aries.symbol: A double promise.
aries.keynote: The realization that fulfillment in any life activity requires the ability to relate and to use polar opposites in a spirit of understanding and complementation.

aries.symbol: A man possessed of more gifts than he can hold.
aries.keynote: Obsession by potentiality.

aries.symbol: Lost opportunity regained in the imagination.
aries.keynote: The development of the mind that is able to assess experience truly.

aries.symbol: A large audience confronts the performer who disappointed its expectations.
aries.keynote: The necessity for mature preparation and self-criticism.

aries.symbol: The music of the spheres.
aries.keynote: A cosmic approach to the basic polarity of existence.

aries.symbol: A duck pond and its brood.
aries.keynote: The realization of natural abundance and the total acceptance of one's own individuality as a gift of Nature.

taurus.symbol: A clear mountain stream.
taurus.keynote: The pure, uncontaminated and spontaneous manifestation of one's own individual character.

taurus.symbol: An electrical storm.
taurus.keynote: The cosmic forces that can be released through the disciplined use of the will.

taurus.symbol: Natural steps lead to a lawn of clover in bloom.
taurus.keynote: The gradual expansion of the individual's field of experience in harmony with natural processes.

taurus.symbol: The rainbow's pot of gold.
taurus.keynote: Riches that come from linking the celestial and the earthly nature.

taurus.symbol: A widow at an open grave.
taurus.keynote: The serenity of soul that comes to those who have triumphed over their passions.

taurus.symbol: A bridge being built across a gorge.
taurus.keynote: The conquest of separativeness through group cooperation.

taurus.symbol: A woman of Samaria comes to draw water from the well.
taurus.keynote: The meeting of the traditional past and of the creative spirit pointing to the future.

taurus.symbol: A sleigh on land uncovered by snow.
taurus.keynote: The value of anticipating future conditions in order to make full use of every opportunity.

taurus.symbol: A Christmas tree decorated.
taurus.keynote: The ability to express joy through the creation of special moments of celebration.

taurus.symbol: A red cross nurse.
taurus.keynote: Self-transcending service.

taurus.symbol: A woman sprinkling new ground.
taurus.keynote: Consecration and dedication to a new work.

taurus.symbol: A young couple window shopping.
taurus.keynote: Craving for new experiences and desire-patterns of consumption.

taurus.symbol: A porter carrying heavy baggage.
taurus.keynote: The inner strength which may be assumed even under the greatest burden.

taurus.symbol: Shellfish groping and children playing.
taurus.keynote: The first stages in the transcendence of personal relationships.

taurus.symbol: A man with a rakish silk hat, muffled against the cold, braves a storm.
taurus.keynote: The courage needed to confront the superiority of natural forces and stand firm against them.

taurus.symbol: An old teacher fails to interest his pupils in traditional knowledge.
taurus.keynote: The difficulty of adjusting oneself to an evolutionary crisis which demands a new form of training.

taurus.symbol: A symbolic battle between 'swords' and 'torches.'
taurus.keynote: Refusing to depend upon the past, the seeker turns his back upon the 'loaded' dice of social and intellectual coercion.

taurus.symbol: A new continent rising out of the ocean.
taurus.keynote: The emergence of new continental life-forms out of the all-mother Sea.

taurus.symbol: A newly formed continent. A continent is revealed after the storms of the past have all dried up.
taurus.keynote: The will to create new forms of existence.

taurus.symbol: Wisps of wing-like clouds streaming across the sky.
taurus.keynote: The awareness of spiritual forces at work.

taurus.symbol: A moving finger points to significant passages in a book.
taurus.keynote: The Karmic function and responsibility implied in all relatedness.

taurus.symbol: White dove flying over troubled waters.
taurus.keynote: The spiritual inspiration that comes to the individual in the overcoming of crisis.

taurus.symbol: A jewelry shop.
taurus.keynote: The utilization of natural resources for the enhancing of the personal sense of worth, of beauty, and of prestige.

taurus.symbol: An Indian warrior riding fiercely, human scalps hanging from his belt.
taurus.keynote: Aggressiveness and emotional mobilization of energies.

taurus.symbol: A large well-kept public park.

taurus.symbol: A Spaniard serenading his senorita.
taurus.keynote: The overcoming of social taboos.

taurus.symbol: An old Indian woman selling the artifacts of her tribe to passers-by.

taurus.symbol: A woman pursued by mature romance.

taurus.symbol: Two cobblers working at a table.
taurus.keynote: The development of skill through practice and cooperation.

taurus.symbol: A peacock parading on the terrace of an old castle.
taurus.keynote: The personal display of inherited gifts.

gemini.symbol: A glass-bottomed boat reveals undersea wonders.

gemini.symbol: Drilling for oil.

gemini.symbol: An old-fashioned well.

gemini.symbol: Aroused strikers surround a factory.

gemini.symbol: A quiver filled with arrows.

gemini.symbol: An airplane performing a nose dive.

gemini.symbol: Newly opened lands offer the pioneer new opportunities for experience.

gemini.symbol: A Negro girl fights for her independence in the city.

gemini.symbol: A great musician at his piano.

gemini.symbol: Bridging physical space and social differences in a telepathic conversation.

gemini.symbol: A woman activist in an emotional speech dramatizing her cause.

gemini.symbol: A large archaic volume reveals a traditional wisdom.

gemini.symbol: A modern cafeteria displays an abundance of food, products of various regions.

gemini.symbol: A labor demonstration.
gemini.keynote: Protest against social inequities.

gemini.symbol: Dancing couples in a harvest festival.
gemini.keynote: The wholesome enjoyment of organic processes and physicality in work and recreation.

gemini.symbol: Three fledglings in a nest high in a tree.

gemini.symbol: Children skating on ice.

gemini.symbol: Winter frost in the woods.

gemini.symbol: A gypsy coming out of the forest.

gemini.symbol: The first mockingbird of spring.

gemini.symbol: Bathing in a mountain stream under a waterfall.
gemini.keynote: A return to the source in response to the call of nature.

cancer.symbol: On a ship the sailors lower an old flag and raise a new one.

cancer.symbol: An automobile wrecked by a train.

cancer.symbol: Two fairies dancing on a moonlit night.

cancer.symbol: A very old man facing a vast dark space to the northeast.

cancer.symbol: A group of people who have overeaten and enjoyed it.

cancer.symbol: A man studying a mandala in front of him, with the help of a very ancient book.
cancer.keynote: Reaching out toward the universal and all encompassing symbols of spiritual reality which fulfill and illumine existence.

cancer.symbol: The seed grows into knowledge and life.
cancer.keynote: The unfoldment of the original experience.

cancer.symbol: A hen scratching for her chicks.
cancer.keynote: The strongly felt urge for individual self-expression and activity in social fields.

cancer.symbol: A priest performing a marriage ceremony.

cancer.symbol: American Indians, performing a ritual to the sun.

cancer.symbol: A famous singer is proving her virtuosity during an operatic performance.

cancer.symbol: A woman awaiting a sailboat.
cancer.keynote: The longing for transcendent new developments in a protected atmosphere.

cancer.symbol: The meeting of a literary society.
cancer.keynote: The cultural and intellectual values of the past are renewed and refined in the present.

cancer.symbol: A woman and two men, castaways from a shipwreck on a deserted island in the South Seas.

cancer.symbol: A dark shadow or mantle thrown suddenly over the right shoulder.
cancer.keynote: The gift of power to meet a weakening of inherent vitality.

cancer.symbol: Guests are reading in the library of a luxurious home.

cancer.symbol: A violent storm in a residential canyon filled with valuable homes.
cancer.keynote: The violent explosion of long-contained forces.

cancer.symbol: A modern Pocahontas.
cancer.keynote: The courage to affirm one's own truth and stand up, alone if need be, for one's ideals.

cancer.symbol: A muse weighing newborn twins in golden scales.

cancer.symbol: A daughter of the American Revolution.

leo.symbol: Blood rushes to a man's head as his vital energies are mobilized under the spur of ambition.

leo.symbol: An epidemic of mumps.

leo.symbol: A woman having her hair bobbed.

leo.symbol: The constellations in the sky.

leo.symbol: Children on a swing in a huge oak tree.

leo.symbol: A houseboat party.

leo.symbol: American Indians performing a ritual to the sun.

leo.symbol: An unsealed letter.
